@atlas C|clay-iter-44-arg-shift-root-cause|@C clay-iter-44-arg-shift-root-cause :: meta [4!]\\n  => \\"Why hetzner run shifts args differently than local hexa --selftest:\\"\\n  => \\"  hexa-resolver routes to hetzner via ssh\\"\\n  => \\"  remote shell adds wrapper args before user args\\"\\n  => \\"  args[0..1] = wrapper, args[2] = script path, args[3..] = user args\\"\\n  => \\"  empirical_anchor_v2 hardcodes args[2]=ticks, args[3]=topo, args[4]=seed\\"\\n  => \\"  → on hetzner: args[2]=script-path (non-int → ticks default 50)\\"\\n  => \\"  → topology shifts to args[3], seed shifts to args[4]\\"\\n  => \\"  → tied user args = 2 instead of 3\\"|atlas.n6|45961|-1|false|false
