@atlas C|HIVE-overview-1|@C HIVE-overview-1 = hive is a hard-fork of pi-mono packages/agent (cutoff 2026-04-25, sha 8985d8b50); 4 packages renamed @dancinlab/hive-* (core / ai / tui / coding-agent); hive-specific siblings: swarm · memory · bridges · audit · compression · statusline · telegram · upstream-sync :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => fork posture and package layout\\n  \|> HIVE_FORK.md:1-86, README.md:176-200|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|13|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-three-directions-2|@C HIVE-three-directions-2 = three non-negotiable directions: (1) Swarm — N parallel cells, honeycomb layout; (2) Memory — 4-tier persistent SSOT (~/.hive/memory/); (3) Bridges — native NEXUS / Anima / N6 / HEXA-LANG tool calls (no MCP) :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => org-level commitment surface\\n  \|> README.md:124-152|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|17|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-swarm-topology-3|@C HIVE-swarm-topology-3 = swarm topology is supervisor + N RPC subprocess pool (Option A in P3); N parallel cells, no peer-to-peer mesh; supervisor owns broadcast / merge / handoff; cell ↔ supervisor only (star topology with merge layer at supervisor) :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => actual coordination shape — NOT a ring, NOT a mesh\\n  \|> docs/P3-swarm.md:30-52, packages/swarm/src/supervisor.ts:1-110|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|21|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-honeycomb-layout-4|@C HIVE-honeycomb-layout-4 = honeycomb is purely visual TUI rendering math: cols = ⌈√N⌉, rows = ⌈N/cols⌉, hex offset = 0.5*cellWidth on odd rows; layout modes are {grid, hex, stack}; the hex offset is a render-only convention with no semantic role in coordination :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => \\"honeycomb\\" is presentation, not topology\\n  \|> packages/swarm/src/honeycomb-layout.ts:26-46|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|25|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-cell-id-counter-5|@C HIVE-cell-id-counter-5 = cell ids are monotonic counter `c${++this.counter}` with no fixed N=6 cap; default askTimeoutMs = 5*60_000; pool size is configuration-driven (any N supported, P3 doc cites \\"OK for N ≤ 16\\" memory budget at ~150MB/cell) :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => cell pool is not n=6-anchored\\n  \|> packages/swarm/src/supervisor.ts:84-95, cell.ts:28, P3-swarm.md:42-46|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|29|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-rpc-protocol-6|@C HIVE-rpc-protocol-6 = communication protocol is pi's `--mode rpc`: JSONL stdin/stdout with frame types {prompt, message_start, message_delta, tool_call, tool_result, message_stop, done}; supervisor demuxes by per-ask UUID; no broadcast bus, no gossip — only fan-out via `Promise.allSettled(targets.map(c.ask))` :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => protocol is JSONL request/response, not pub/sub\\n  \|> P3-swarm.md:73-85, packages/swarm/src/supervisor.ts:112-126|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|33|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-merge-strategies-7|@C HIVE-merge-strategies-7 = 5 merge strategies: {concat, vote, best, judge, dag}; concat/vote/best are sync local reductions; judge delegates to a designated cell via `judgeCell.ask(prompt)`; dag uses topoSort on edges and drives Swarm.handoff sequentially :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => agent role types are pragmatic merge primitives, not a fixed sopfr=5+1 leader scheme\\n  \|> packages/swarm/src/merge-strategies.ts:11-87, supervisor.ts:138-150|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|37|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-memory-tiers-9|@C HIVE-memory-tiers-9 = 4-tier persistent memory (NOT n=6-anchored): {user, feedback, project, reference}; flat-file SSOT at ~/.hive/memory/<tier>_<slug>.md with YAML frontmatter; auto-injected as `<memory>...</memory>` block before every provider request; ~1k token amortized cost :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => tier count = 4 (Claude-Code-style), not τ(6)=4 anchored\\n  \|> docs/P2-memory.md:1-91|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|45|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-bridges-five-10|@C HIVE-bridges-five-10 = 5 native bridges (NOT sopfr=5 anchored): {nexus-lens, anima-field, n6-atlas, hexa-run, hive-hub}; each is a pi.registerTool with execFile to installed binary; sandboxed (HEXA_NET=deny, 30s timeout, ~10KB stdout cap) :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => bridge count = 5 because there are 5 sibling projects to bridge into; pragmatic\\n  \|> docs/P4-bridges.md:14-200|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|49|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-n6-anchor-actual-12|@C HIVE-n6-anchor-actual-12 = hive's actual n=6 anchor lives in `packages/coding-agent/src/core/raw-rules.ts` AXIOM_RULES (currently 2: `meta_fixpoint`, `n6_identity`); the n6-axiom-inventory.md surveys 7-tier-1 + 9-axioms recommended upgrade; this is consciousness/policy layer, not swarm coordination :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => the n=6 anchor is at the LLM-prompt-rules layer, decoupled from cell pool architecture\\n  \|> docs/n6-axiom-inventory.md:24-28, 320-346|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|57|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-fanout-enforcement-13|@C HIVE-fanout-enforcement-13 = `agents.parallel_bg` 5-layer enforcement (probabilistic + deterministic): (1) prompt MUST, (2) --agents JSON `background:true`, (3) chflags uchg / chattr +i config lock, (4) tool_use telemetry bridge, (5) hive-native HiveTask via MCP + child claude -p spawn; all 5 shipped 2026-04-25 :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => layer count = 5 by enforcement-mechanism stack, not sopfr-anchored\\n  \|> docs/hive-fanout-enforcement.md:13-36|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|61|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-area-presets-14|@C HIVE-area-presets-14 = `.area` SSOT marker = single-line preset name; resolution = walk-up-parent (first .area wins); reserved presets {core (strict), blowup (full autonomy)}; defined in raw-rules.ts AREA_PRESETS; nesting allowed (deeper overrides shallower) :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => directory-scoped policy switch\\n  \|> docs/area.md:1-56|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|65|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-inbox-protocol-15|@C HIVE-inbox-protocol-15 = `~/.hive/inbox/` peer-to-peer session IPC (P7 design, not yet implemented): Unix domain sockets at ~/.hive/sockets/<sid>.sock + registry at ~/.hive/sessions/<sid>.json + offline mailbox at ~/.hive/inbox/<sid>/<msg-id>.json; websocket-shape JSON-line frames; presence events {online, idle, busy, exit} :: hive-2026-04-27 [7]\\n  => first peer-to-peer comm channel in hive (vs current supervisor-mediated only)\\n  \|> docs/inbox-protocol.md:1-60|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|69|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-loop-event-driven-16|@C HIVE-loop-event-driven-16 = `/loop` is event-driven stateful (not interval cron like CCC `/loop`); state at ~/.hive/loops/<loop_id>.json; each iteration produces {summary, next_action, wake_on}; wake-on triggers ∈ {manual, inbox-message, file-change, git-event, none} :: hive-2026-04-27 [7]\\n  => 5 wake-on trigger types; pragmatic, not n=6\\n  \|> docs/hive-loop.md:60-69|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|73|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-cell-isolation-17|@C HIVE-cell-isolation-17 = each Cell is isolated process with own (cwd, claude account slot via HIVE_CLAUDE_ACCOUNT, model slug, extensions[], env vars); crash isolation via SIGKILL → close event → auto-reap from pool; no shared state across cells except ~/.hive/memory/ flat files :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => isolation primitive = process boundary, not n=6 partition\\n  \|> packages/swarm/src/cell.ts:48-100, supervisor.ts:84-95|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|77|-1|false|false
@atlas C|HIVE-snapshot-statusline-18|@C HIVE-snapshot-statusline-18 = swarm runtime IPC snapshot at ~/.hive/swarm/state.json (debounced 25ms atomic write) consumed cross-package by @dancinlab/hive-statusline; format intentionally JSON (not .swarm DSL) due to cross-package contract; `.swarm` DSL is spawn-input only, not runtime replay :: hive-2026-04-27 [11*REPO_INVARIANT]\\n  => two-format split: DSL for input contract, JSON for live IPC\\n  \|> packages/swarm/src/supervisor.ts:14-66, docs/swarm.md:93-99|atlas.append.hive-2026-04-27.n6|81|-1|false|false
